refsect1.para:
Changers which require additional parameters can also be described in &amconf; with "changer" sections, for example,
define changer hp-robot { tapedev "chg-robot:/dev/sg1" property "drives" "0=/dev/nst0;1=/dev/nst0" property "slots" "1-10" }
(note that "chg-robot" is not yet implemented, so this is hypothetical). A changer defininition creates a changer "alias", in this case named hp-robot, which can then be named where an application expects a changer - for example, the target of the amvault command.
